In assembly orders it is available configurator management. The configurator opens manually by action or automatically on item validation. 

<img width="" src="https://docs-test.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR001094-0/AssemblyOrdersConf-ENU.png"><br>

To be able to configure, it is necessary to have an item with: 
* **"Neutral to Configuration"** as type;
* a **rule**;
* **"Assembly"** as replenishment system;
* an **Assembly BOM**. 

<img width="" src="https://docs-test.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR001094-0/ItemChar1-ENU.png"><br>
<img width="" src="https://docs-test.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR001094-0/ItemChar2-ENU.png"><br>
<img width="" src="https://docs-test.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR001094-0/ItemAssemblyBOM-ENU.png"><br>